{"parse":{"title":"Bremen clause","pageid":12545207,"revid":773874456,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Bremen clause</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/German_language\" title=\"German language\">German</a>: <i><span lang=\"de\">Bremer Klausel</span></i>) is Article 141 of the <a href=\"/wiki/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\" title=\"Basic Law for the Federal Republic of Germany\">Basic Law for the Federal Republic of Germany</a>, which states:\n</p>\n<table class=\"cquote pullquote\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"margin:auto; border-collapse: collapse; border: none; background-color: transparent; width: auto;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20px; vertical-align: top; border: none; color: #B2B7F2; font-size: 40px; font-family: &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, Times, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: .6em; text-align: left; padding: 10px 10px;\">\u201c\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top; border: none; padding: 4px 10px;\"><i>Artikel 7 Abs. 3 Satz 1 findet keine Anwendung in einem Lande, in dem am 1. Januar 1949 eine andere landesrechtliche Regelung bestand.</i>\n<p>The first sentence of paragraph (3) of Article 7 shall not apply in any state in which, on January 1, 1949, state law provides otherwise.\n</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 20px; vertical-align: bottom; border: none; color: #B2B7F2; font-size: 40px; font-family: &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, Times, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: .6em; text-align: right; padding: 10px 10px;\">\u201d\n</td></tr>\n\n</tbody></table>\n<p>The sentence there cited says:\n</p>\n<table class=\"cquote pullquote\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"margin:auto; border-collapse: collapse; border: none; background-color: transparent; width: auto;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20px; vertical-align: top; border: none; color: #B2B7F2; font-size: 40px; font-family: &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, Times, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: .6em; text-align: left; padding: 10px 10px;\">\u201c\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top; border: none; padding: 4px 10px;\"><i>Der Religionsunterricht ist in den \u00f6ffentlichen Schulen mit Ausnahme der bekenntnisfreien Schulen ordentliches Lehrfach.</i>\n<p>Religious instruction shall form part of the regular curriculum in state schools, with the exception of non-denominational schools.\n</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 20px; vertical-align: bottom; border: none; color: #B2B7F2; font-size: 40px; font-family: &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, Times, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: .6em; text-align: right; padding: 10px 10px;\">\u201d\n</td></tr>\n\n</tbody></table>\n<p>It limits the range of application of the constitutional (Basic Law) rule over <a href=\"/wiki/Religious_education\" title=\"Religious education\">religious education</a>, making it possible to have other types of instruction in some areas of <a href=\"/wiki/Germany\" title=\"Germany\">Germany</a>. A well-known example is the \"instruction in <a href=\"/wiki/Bible\" title=\"Bible\">Biblical</a> history\" in <a href=\"/wiki/Bremen\" title=\"Bremen\">Bremen</a>. It is not religious education in the sense of the Basic Law, because its content is not accountable to a <a href=\"/wiki/Religious_community\" title=\"Religious community\">religious community</a>; therefore it is not a \"<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Common_affair&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Common affair (page does not exist)\">common affair</a>\" (<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Res_mixta&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Res mixta (page does not exist)\">res mixta</a>).\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><span style=\"vertical-align: middle; background:transparent\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_Germany.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flag of Germany\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Flag_of_Germany.svg/30px-Flag_of_Germany.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"18\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Flag_of_Germany.svg/45px-Flag_of_Germany.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Flag_of_Germany.svg/60px-Flag_of_Germany.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1000\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a><span style=\"margin-left:-30px;\"><img alt=\"Justice icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Scale_of_justice_2.svg/29px-Scale_of_justice_2.svg.png\" width=\"29\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Scale_of_justice_2.svg/44px-Scale_of_justice_2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Scale_of_justice_2.svg/59px-Scale_of_justice_2.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"204\" data-file-height=\"208\" /></span></span></td><td><i>This article about <a href=\"/wiki/Law_of_Germany\" title=\"Law of Germany\">German law</a> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Bremen_clause&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Germany-law-stub\" title=\"Template:Germany-law-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Germany-law-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Germany-law-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Germany-law-stub&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2175\nCached time: 20180921233230\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.132 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.166 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 261/1